race.description: Gilgandra Services Club Gilgandra Cup Handicap
race.comment: HOW'S IT KEV (3) tough miler who comes out of a strong contest after he closed late with a respectable third over 1600m at Warwick Farm in BM72 class. Deep into the prep and can finish over the top of these. ROUGE MOULIN (6) consistent gelding who indicated a win was imminent when a game on-pace second with the 61kg over this trip at Dubbo. Nose roll comes off and will prove hard to run down with the 55kg. AIMPOINT (1) smart type who can make sharp improvement at his third run back after fading quickly when last over 1550m at Canterbury in BM72 grade. Claim helps from the low draw, respect. TURGENEV (8) strips fitter with a leading apprentice booked from the good gate. Proven at the mile and assess on his good second at Orange two starts back. TAINUI (4) drops in trip and weight and assess on his solid win in the Cotton Cup over this trip two starts back. Keep safe.
